{"word":"ἐπαίω","slug":"ἐπαίω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπαίω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> <el>ἐπᾴω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to give ear to</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to perceive, feel</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to understand</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>to profess knowledge, to be a professor</i> in any subject, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}